<LanguageData>
  
  <!-- EN: chemfuel silo -->
  <DMSE_FuelSiloTank.label>液态燃料筒仓</DMSE_FuelSiloTank.label>
  <!-- EN: A large storage tank for storing liquid fuels uses multiple layers of metal plates and special alloys to store pressurized liquefied fuel within the tank. It provides robust protection while also holding a large amount of fuel. supplie for thrusters on a gravship. -->
  <DMSE_FuelSiloTank.description>一种用於储存液态燃料的大型储槽，采用多层金属板与特殊合金结构，可在槽体内安全存放加压液化燃料。它在提供良好防护的同时也为重力船上的推进器供应大量燃料。</DMSE_FuelSiloTank.description>
  <!-- EN: Chemfuel -->
  <DMSE_FuelSiloTank.comps.CompRefuelable.fuelGizmoLabel>化合燃料</DMSE_FuelSiloTank.comps.CompRefuelable.fuelGizmoLabel>
  <!-- EN: Chemfuel -->
  <DMSE_FuelSiloTank.comps.CompRefuelable.fuelLabel>液态燃料</DMSE_FuelSiloTank.comps.CompRefuelable.fuelLabel>
  
  <!-- EN: Fusion reactor -->
  <DMSE_FusionCore.label>聚变反应炉</DMSE_FusionCore.label>
  <!-- EN: A highly mature compact tokamak fusion reactor, commonly found in colonial fleets and ships used in the Enlightened World, has a built-in supercritical carbon dioxide turbine to provide power for its own cycle and ship equipment. However, its most crucial function is to preheat the ship's nuclear thermal propulsion system so that it can reach its maximum design power to move small-mass celestial bodies. -->
  <DMSE_FusionCore.description>一种高度成熟的紧凑型托卡马克聚变反应炉，常见於殖民舰队与启明世界所使用的各式舰船。其内建超临界二氧化碳涡轮，可为自身循环系统与船舰设备提供电力。不过，它最关键的用途是为船舰的核热推进系统进行预热，使其能达到最大设计功率，以推动小质量天体。</DMSE_FusionCore.description>
  
  <!-- EN: Nuclear thermal thruster -->
  <DMSE_NuclearThruster.label>核热推进器</DMSE_NuclearThruster.label>
  <!-- EN: A heavy nuclear-thermal rocket thruster that generates thrust by heating liquid hydrogen through nuclear Fusion. Its specific impulse is more than twice that of conventional chemical rockets. These high-thrust engines are commonly used on interstellar tugs to perform major orbital transfers for massive platforms. Because launch operation produces substantial radioactive contamination, this engine is designed for non-atmospheric use only.\n\nBefore the Tanaka-Johnson drive was introduced, humanity used this class of thruster to accelerate the first sublight ship to the Alpha Centauri system to 20% of light speed, and received the first selfie from outside the Solar System ten years later. -->
  <DMSE_NuclearThruster.description>一种重型核热火箭推进器，透过核分裂加热液态氢来产生推力，其比冲是传统化学火箭推进器的两倍以上。这类大推力推进器经常用於星际拖船，使其能为质量庞大的轨道平台进行较大幅度的轨道转移。由於起飞时会制造大量放射性污染，这类引擎被设计为无法在大气环境内使用。\n\n在田中-约翰逊引擎问世以前，人类便是透过这种推进器将第一艘前往半人马座星系的亚光速飞船加速到光速的 20%，并在 10 年後传回人类於太阳系外的第一张自拍照。</DMSE_NuclearThruster.description>
  
  <!-- EN: rocket booster -->
  <DMSE_SolidRocketThruster.label>火箭助推器</DMSE_SolidRocketThruster.label>
  <!-- EN: A simple and reliable disposable thruster. It provides thrust by premixing fuel and oxidizer into a solid propellant grain, which burns upon ignition to generate high-temperature gas. It has a rapid start-up capability. It is commonly used as a rocket booster or initial propulsion for strategic missiles on many pre-spacer planets, and is also frequently used as a temporary range extension for small and medium-sized ships during suborbital flight. -->
  <DMSE_SolidRocketThruster.description>一种结构简单且可靠的一次性推进器。它将燃料与氧化剂预先混合为固体推进药柱，点火後燃烧产生高温燃气以提供推力，具备快速启动的特性。在许多前太空时代星球上，它常被用作火箭助推器或战略飞弹的初始动力，也常作为中小型舰船进行亚轨道飞行时的临时增程手段。</DMSE_SolidRocketThruster.description>
  
</LanguageData>